1 (2) (I) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS
2 PARAGRAPH, A CELLULAR PHONE CONFISCATED FROM A STUDENT IN ACCORDANCE
3 WITH PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION MUST BE RETRIEVED BY THE STUDENT’S
4 PARENT OR GUARDIAN.
5 (II) IF A STUDENT’S PARENT OR GUARDIAN NOTIFIES THE
6 SCHOOL THAT THE PARENT OR GUARDIAN IS UNABLE TO RETRIEVE THE STUDENT’S
7 CONFISCATED CELLULAR PHONE, THE SCHOOL SHALL RETURN THE CELLULAR
8 PHONE TO THE STUDENT AT THE END OF THE SCHOOL DAY.
